textMap.PRIMARY: Bonus Content: This episode of "The Man in the High Castle" is one of a number of titles that benefit from exclusive videos and behind-the-scenes photos, accessible in the X-Ray Bonus tab in Prime Video.
The most common mode of execution in the Japanese Pacific States is by firing squad. Nakamura's death by bayonet is, therefore, demonstrative of Kido's extreme contempt for his treacherous actions.

According to Alexa Davalos, the arrival of the alternate-world Trudy at the end of Season 2 makes it even easier for Juliana to accept what she already believed to be true about the multiverse. Nevertheless, it is difficult for other characters in "The Man in the High Castle" to believe the truth, even when presented with the films from another world.

The Josef Mengele character in "The Man in the High Castle" is based on the Josef Mengele from our history. Mengele was an SS officer and medical physician known for depraved experimentation on prisoners.

In Philip K. Dick's book, Juliana Crain visits a Denver that seems to function like a regular American city. In the TV series, the creative team imagined a more run-down, impoverished and dangerous version of the Zone, partly to explain why everyone doesn't go there to escape the rule of the Axis powers.

Growing up wealthy and privileged in the Berlin countryside, young Nicole was completed shielded from the realities of the European, Pacific and Rebel American wars. Nevertheless, she was mildly affected by the disappearance of two Lebensborn friends in 1960; after being taken in by the Gestapo for questioning, they were never seen again. Nicole, was questioned and released after three days.

The original version of the script contained more dialogue between Frank and Juliana during the scene when they reunite at Sabra. Alexa Davalos has said that she prefers the quiet truthfulness of the moment that comes across in the version that made it on screen.

It's significant that the film of the Allies winning the Second World War shows footage of Winston Churchill and Franklin Roosevelt; in the alt-timeline both Roosevelt and Churchill were assassinated - Roosevelt in 1933, Churchill in 1940.

Juliana, Ed and Frank have been best friends for several years. Though Frank and Juliana's relationship initially made Ed jealous, he quickly came to love Juliana just as much as Frank did, and Juliana took to Ed immediately.
Culturally, the Japanese see white Americans as a 'surrendered" and therefore 'shamed' race. They are beneath contempt.

Philip K. Dick began work on a sequel to the book "The Man in the High Castle" that further explores the Nazi plot to break into and colonize alternate worlds with the Nebenwelt machine. The narrative was never completed.

Independent small businesses that cater to the Japanese elite market do well in San Francisco, but the majority of whites and non-Japanese work in low-wage jobs that barely help them scrape by. Childan's Emporium, made him a rare exception to the rule.

The conversation between Kido and Tagomi at end of Episode 307 takes on a very different feel from other conversations set in the Kempetai offices, in part because nightfall makes this familiar environment feel like another world. Over the course of three seasons, this is the first time Inspector Kido's office has been shown at night.

The Nazis were obsessed with advanced engineering, science and genetics in real-world history. They are similarly obsessed in "The Man in the High Castle" and their defeat of Europe and North America has cemented their dominance as the foremost technological power on the globe.
